  "chapter": {
    "number": 9,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Destruction of Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "I saw the Lord standing beside the altar, and He said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Strike the tops of the pillars",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that the thresholds shake.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Topple them on the heads of all the people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will kill the rest with the sword.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "None of those who flee will get away;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "none of the fugitives will escape.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though they dig down to Sheol,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from there My hand will take them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and though they climb up to heaven,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from there I will pull them down.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though they hide themselves atop Carmel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there I will track them and seize them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and though they hide from Me at the bottom of the sea,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there I will command the serpent",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1326
          },
          {
            "text": "to bite them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though they are driven by their enemies into captivity,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there I will command the sword to slay them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will fix My eyes upon them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for harm and not for good.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Lord GOD of Hosts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He who touches the earth and it melts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and all its dwellers mourn—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all the land rises like the Nile,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then sinks like the river of Egypt—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He builds His upper rooms in the heavens",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and founds His vault upon the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He summons the waters of the sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pours them over the face of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD is His name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Are you not like the Cushites",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1327
          },
          {
            "text": "to Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O children of Israel?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD.",
          {
            "text": "“Did I not bring Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "up from the land of Egypt,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the Philistines from Caphtor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1328
          },
          {
            "text": "and the Arameans from Kir?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely the eyes of the Lord GOD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are on the sinful kingdom,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will destroy it from the face of the earth.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet I will not utterly destroy the house of Jacob,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“For surely I will give the command,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will shake the house of Israel",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "among all the nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as grain is sifted in a sieve;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but not a pebble will reach the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the sinners among My people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will die by the sword—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all those who say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Disaster will never draw near or confront us.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Promise of Restoration"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“In that day I will restore",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fallen tent of David.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will repair its gaps, restore its ruins,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rebuild it as in the days of old,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "that they may possess the remnant of Edom",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all the nations that bear My name,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1329
          },
          "declares the LORD, who will do this."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Behold, the days are coming,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“when the plowman will overtake the reaper",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the treader of grapes, the sower of seed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The mountains will drip with sweet wine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with which all the hills will flow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will restore My people Israel from captivity;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1330
          },
          {
            "text": "they will rebuild and inhabit the ruined cities.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will plant vineyards and drink their wine;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will make gardens and eat their fruit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will firmly plant them in their own land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "never again to be uprooted",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "from the land that I have given them,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "says the LORD your God."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 1326,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Hebrew nachash; translated in most cases as snake",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 9,
          "verse": 3
        }
      },
      {
